  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Class: WARD OPERATIONAL PLAN - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
This is a statement of the operational planning intent for a particular 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>, including intended time and 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_bed">Hospital Bed</xref>
 availability, 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_treatment_function">TREATMENT FUNCTION</xref>
 and 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_clinical_care_intensity">CLINICAL CARE INTENSITY</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_bed">Hospital Bed</xref>
 availability, in the above, is expressed as the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>
 Total Beds Intended (<xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_consultant">CONSULTANT</xref>
 Care, 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_nurse">NURSE</xref>
 Care and 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_midwife">MIDWIFE</xref>
 Care) available for the use of 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>. This should reflect the number of places available for 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 care rather than just a count of physical devices that may be used as a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_bed">Hospital Bed</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
